3. Object Code Incorporating Material from Library Header Files.

The object code form of an Application may incorporate material from a header file that is part of the Library. You may convey such object code under terms of your choice, provided that, if the incorporated material is not limited to numerical parameters, data structure layouts, accessors, or small macros, then you must:

a) Convey the Minimal Corresponding Source under the terms of this License, and the Corresponding Application Code in a form suitable for linking with the Library.

b) Accompany the work with a written offer, valid for at least three years, to give the recipient all the materials needed to rebuild the work using the Library.

c) If the work is conveyed via physical product, accompany it with a copy of the written offer.

d) Do not restrict reverse engineering of the work beyond what is allowed by applicable law.

4. Combined Works.

You may convey a Combined Work under terms of your choice that, taken together, do not restrict modification of the portions of the Library contained in the Combined Work and reverse engineering for debugging such modifications.

